@kaxil we have a use case that we want to override the params during backfill and trigger_dag.

We can pass some key-value pairs through `backfill -c '{"text": "blah blah"}'`
or `trigger_dag -c '{"text": "blah blah"}'`
and it will override the value in {{ params.text }}

@tedmiston - Agreed - We pinned our cookbook like this:
'>=4.1.0, <4.2.0'
https://github.com/bahchis/airflow-cookbook/pull/22/files#diff-63da1eb5d35a0fe1016e58ed5c24ad9eR20

@bolkedebruin 6 months ago you unconditionally added `visibility_timeout` to default_airflow.cfg:

https://github.com/apache/incubator-airflow/commit/aa737a582c687e7105ef934ffc4da3dc78438235

This works for Redis and SQS celery broker transports, but breaks others,  which don't support this option, (especially sqlalchemy).  So, to preserve the existing behavior of what was there for Redis and SQS, but to not break sqlalchemy, I inserted the checks in default_celery.py

@Fokko I agree, however there is this comment:

https://github.com/NielsZeilemaker/incubator-airflow/blob/94407ff9bdee35e70bd385fdc752066d87e83e2c/airflow/config_templates/airflow_local_settings.py#L24

Which seems to want to split the logging config and the configuration, and hence I implemented it in this manner. I don't agree with the TODO btw.

